.foo[.baz]
}}}
INPUT = {{{
{"foo":{"bar":4},"baz":"bar"}
}}}
GOLD = {{{
4
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$py=_['foo'][_['baz']]"}
}}}
COMMENT=Runtime subscript using another field's value as the key — different from the object-construction "computed key" limitation (that one was about building keys, this is about reading with a dynamic key, which subscripting handles fine).

