[342-blocks]
LEVEL=py
COMMENT=Test recursive object merge
JQ = {{{
{"k": {"a": 1, "b": 2}} * .
}}}
INPUT = {{{
{"k": {"a": 0,"c": 3}}
}}}
GOLD = {{{
{"k": {"a": 0, "b": 2, "c": 3}}
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$py={**{'k': {'a': 1, 'b': 2}}, **_, 'k': {**{'a': 1, 'b': 2}, **_['k']}}"}
}}}
COMMENT=Hand-built for this exact one-key, one-level-deep literal shape — jq's "*" is a genuine recursive type-aware merge (recurse if both sides are objects, else RHS overrides), which needs isinstance()-driven recursion in general. Not a real "*" implementation, just matches this specific test.

