}}}
SKIP=needs try/catch.

[357-blocks]
LEVEL=run
JQ = {{{
flatten
}}}
INPUT = {{{
[0, [1], [[2]], [[[3]]]]
}}}
GOLD = {{{
[0, 1, 2, 3]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyrun=result = list(_)\nwhile any(isinstance(x, list) for x in result):\n    new_result = []\n    for item in result:\n        if isinstance(item, list):\n            new_result.extend(item)\n        else:\n            new_result.append(item)\n    result = new_result\nreturn result"}
}}}
COMMENT=Unlimited-depth flatten via a while-loop that keeps expanding until no list remains — genuinely general (no depth assumption), no recursion needed since it's iterative widening rather than depth-first recursion.

